"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-entertainment-2024-0726-1462099-celine-dion-makes-return-to-performance-at-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Celine Dion has given her first live public performance since revealing she is living with stiff person syndrome (SPS), with a spectacular rendition from the Eiffel Tower at the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9117325012120237e-59, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 114, \"end\": 117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"score\": 0.7399958509582883, \"rank\": 0.28462768603467326, \"text\": \"SPS\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The superstar closed the ceremony from the first stage of the French landmark, singing Edith Piaf'sL'Hymne A L'Amour.\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Canadian singer cancelled her Las Vegas residency due to health concerns in 2021, before revealing her SPS diagnosis in December 2022 and cancelling her Courage World Tour.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9962525705119502, \"rank\": 0.0037588864669369938, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 374, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"score\": 0.998931782193784, \"rank\": 0.0010693579477530518, \"text\": \"Las Vegas\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 447, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"score\": 0.7399958509582883, \"rank\": 0.28462768603467326, \"text\": \"SPS\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courage_World_Tour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Courage World Tour\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courage_World_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courage_World_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She appeared in the final moments of the Olympics pageantry dressed in a beaded silver gown with a high neckline and appeared emotional as she came to the climax of the song.\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dion's rare condition which causes progressive muscular inflexibility.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her struggles are documented in her 2024 documentaryI Am: Celine Dion, in which she spoke about her desire to return to performing.\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier in the ceremony, US singer Lady Gaga surprised viewers by singing in French during her performance of the classicMon Truc En Plume.\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.9938646508677417, \"rank\": 0.003868785205843393, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}, {\"begin\": 934, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1024, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Truc\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Truc\"}, {\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plume_(publisher)\", \"score\": 0.8809367731320711, \"rank\": 0.06405228758169043, \"text\": \"Plume\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plume_(publisher)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plume_(publisher)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After her rendition she said it was her \\\"supreme honour\\\" to perform at the event.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On X, formerly Twitter, she said: \\\"I feel so completely grateful to have been asked to open the Paris @Olympics 2024 this year.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.41478107021108e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am also humbled to be asked by the Olympics organising committee to sing such a special French song - a song to honour the French people and their tremendous history of art, music, and theatre.\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1343, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1378, \"end\": 1391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This song was sung by Zizi Jeanmaire, born in Paris a French ballerina, she famously sangMon Truc En Plumesin 1961.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1473, \"end\": 1487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zizi Jeanmaire\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\"}, {\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.41478107021108e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The title means My Thing With Feathers.\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And this is not the first time we have crossed paths.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Zizi starred in Cole Porter's musicalAnything Goeswhich was my first jazz release.\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.690726514264381e-15, \"text\": \"Zizi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Although I am not a French artist, I have always felt a very special connection with French people and singing French music.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1772, \"end\": 1778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1837, \"end\": 1850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1863, \"end\": 1869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wanted nothing more than to create a performance that would warm the heart of France, celebrate French art and music, and on such a momentous occasion remind everyone of one of the most magical cities on earth - Paris.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 2099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999997557552, \"rank\": 2.2972095233432094e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1977, \"end\": 1983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2093, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.41478107021108e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We rented pom poms from Le Lido archive - a real French cabaret theatre.\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2151, \"end\": 2157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We collaborated with Dior to create custom costumes, using naturally moulted feathers.\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I studied French choreography that put a modern twist on a French classic.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2323, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French classic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I rehearsed tirelessly to study a joyful French dance, brushing up on some old skills - I bet you did not know I used to dance at a 60s French party on the lower east side when I was first starting out.\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2382, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope you love this performance as much as I do.\", \"from\": 2545, \"to\": 2595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And to everyone in France, thank you so much for welcoming me to your country to sing in honour of you - it's a gift I will never forget.\\\"\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2615, \"end\": 2621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999997557552, \"rank\": 2.2972095233432094e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The singer congratulated the athletes who are competing and added that it was her \\\"supreme honour\\\" to sing for them.\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening her performance, Gaga emerged from a plume of pink feathers as she sang alongside a group of dancers while wearing a black bodice with a detachable black and pink ruffled skirt.\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2879, \"end\": 2883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.853246616287097e-47, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The singer, real name Stefani Germanotta, performed next to the River Seine, near the Notre Dame cathedral, during the first opening ceremony to be staged outside a stadium.\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3063, \"end\": 3081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefani Germanotta\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 3105, \"end\": 3116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the ceremony moved down the river, it paid tribute to the country's culture and history includingLes Miserables, the popular novel by Victor Hugo, which is also a smash hit musical.\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hugo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6762251712880075e-48, \"text\": \"Victor Hugo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hugo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hugo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following a sequence paying homage to the historical epic, French heavy metal band Gojira performed at the Conciergerie, a former courthouse and prison in the city.\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3461, \"end\": 3467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3485, \"end\": 3491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.051485882885722e-28, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 3509, \"end\": 3521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.860412547658687e-34, \"text\": \"Conciergerie\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the other performers was French-Malian singer Aya Nakamura, who sang while dressed in a golden dress paired with gladiator boots and gold jewellery.\", \"from\": 3568, \"to\": 3722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The celebrations were met with heavy rain with performers, including pianist Alexandre Kantorow, braving heavy showers during their performances.\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3801, \"end\": 3819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexandre Kantorow\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A catwalk show of French fashions was also a rather soggy affair.\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 3936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3889, \"end\": 3895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7425621518909601, \"rank\": 0.3448707522034192, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other performances included Sofiane Pamart and Juliette Armanet delivering a rendition of John Lennon'sImagine.\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 4049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3985, \"end\": 4001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliette_Armanet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Juliette Armanet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliette_Armanet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliette_Armanet\"}, {\"begin\": 4028, \"end\": 4039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Lennon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.484983567191285e-16, \"text\": \"John Lennon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Lennon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Lennon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of 85 boats carried the team delegations on a four-mile journey through the centre of Paris, with more than 300,000 spectators lining the banks of the river.\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4145, \"end\": 4150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.41478107021108e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Celebrities includingWickedstar Ariana Grande and American singer Pharrell Williams appeared at a red carpet event prior to the ceremony.\", \"from\": 4218, \"to\": 4355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4268, \"end\": 4276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999996843262623, \"rank\": 3.077086209458879e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4284, \"end\": 4301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pharrell_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pharrell Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pharrell_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pharrell_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Source: Press Association    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 4357, \"to\": 4397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 4398, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4423, \"end\": 4446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851270567, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 4448, \"end\": 4455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999570932241, \"rank\": 4.29068492243155e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.or